    <item>
      <title>Punch Back! - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/12/07/punch-back/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/12/07/punch-back/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 08 Dec 2024 04:59:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13141" class="post-13141 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Punch Back!&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, I found a new house in town. Jeremiah&amp;#8217;s replacement has moved in, and it&amp;#8217;s Punchy the cat!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8087-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Punchy: Nice to meetcha! I'm Punchy, and I'm so happy to finally meet someone from this town!" class="wp-image-13142" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Punchy lived here before in 2019-20, and more recently, in my New Horizons town from 2022 until May of this year. I like him, but I&amp;#8217;m not crazy about him like some people seem to be. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Big Top and Ruby had both asked me for fossils, and I fulfilled both of those requests today. I gave Big Top an archaeopteryx, and he said it could sleep with him tonight!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8090-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Big Top: Huh huh huh huh! My little archaeopteryx can sleep with me tonight!" class="wp-image-13143" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;He gave me 528 bells for it.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;If you thought &lt;em&gt;his &lt;/em&gt;reaction was a little odd, check out what Ruby said when I gave her a pachy tail. She said it was her &lt;em&gt;new love&lt;/em&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8091-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Ruby: Whoo! My pachy tail! My new love!" class="wp-image-13144" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;She gave me a stroller in return.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Punchy asked me for some festive clothes for the holidays, and the folk shirt at Able Sisters definitely seemed to fit the bill. I took it over to Punchy, and he liked it. He rewarded me with a lovely carpet.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8093-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Punchy: I can't believe you got me a folk shirt..." class="wp-image-13145" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It seemed like &lt;em&gt;everyone &lt;/em&gt;was asking me for help tonight! Robin wanted a bagworm, and Midge needed her house key fished out of the river. I helped out both birds.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8089-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Robin: Is this...? It IS! You brought the bagworm I wanted!" class="wp-image-13147" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8092-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="Midge: Oh...! Awesome! Yes, this is my key, I eat bugs!" class="wp-image-13146" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Robin rewarded me with a plush carpet, while Midge slipped me a slim quazoid.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Whether it was for fossils, fashion, or fishing, I fulfilled five favors for friends tonight! So I took it easy the rest of the night, enjoying K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show at the Roost. I asked for a random song, and he performed K.K. Waltz for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8094-sm-150x80.jpg" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Waltz." class="wp-image-13148" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2024/12/07/punch-back/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-12-07T23:59:00-05:00"&gt;December 7, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-12-08T00:47:01-05:00"&gt;December 8, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/RUU_8087-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Toasty Time Machine - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/12/07/toasty-time-machine/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/12/07/toasty-time-machine/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 08 Dec 2024 04:37:36 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8486" class="post-8486 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Toasty Time Machine&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, Pascal told me that he would like a machine that can un-toast bread! That would basically be a time machine! Just&amp;#8230;a kinda &lt;em&gt;crumb-y&lt;/em&gt; one.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/pascal-toast-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Pascal: I want a machine that turns toast back into soft bread. I've got too many toast regrets, maaan..." class="wp-image-8489" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He also took my scallop and gave me some mermaid shoes. I&amp;#8217;m just trying to figure out how a mermaid would actually wear these, since they don&amp;#8217;t have feet.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Gullivarrr was also in town, and I recovered his phone for him. To thank me, he sent me a pirate-treasure crown the next day.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, Merengue was sick with a cold. I crafted some medicine for her, and she started to feel better. She thanked me by giving me a sushi chef&amp;#8217;s outfit.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/merengue-sushi-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Merengue: I'd like to thank you by giving you a sushi chef's outfit." class="wp-image-8490" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I don&amp;#8217;t plan on wearing it, but it was a &lt;em&gt;rice &lt;/em&gt;gesture. 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Merengue was back to her usual self. But she was having trouble coming up with a dinner plan&amp;#8230;unless her catchphrase is actually her suggestion. 😉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/merengue-dinner-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Merengue: I'm struggling to come up with a last-minute dinner plan, a berry..." class="wp-image-8491" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;That&amp;#8217;s a berry light meal!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Rodney the rodent was camping at the campsite, and I had no interest in the pest. He also camped here back in 2021, if anyone is interested in that fact. (Doubt it, haha.)&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/rodney-camper2-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Rodney: Heya! Are you from around here? I'm kinda on vacation, just relaxing and focus-grouping a few things..." class="wp-image-8492" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;When you&amp;#8217;re done, hop back on your wheel and roll out.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tonight, there was a decent crowd for K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s concert. Rio, Ketchup, and Merengue joined me for a performance of Agent K.K. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="393" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/kk-12724-250x140.jpg" alt="K.K. Slider performs for Rio, Ketchup, Jeff, and Merengue." class="wp-image-8488" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Curiously, Agent S was nowhere to be found for the agent-themed song. Unless she was undercover, hiding in plain sight somewhere nearby! 🕵️‍♀️&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/12/07/toasty-time-machine/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-12-07T23:37:36-05:00"&gt;December 7, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-12-07T23:37:37-05:00"&gt;December 7, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/pascal-toast-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Telling Gulliver No - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/12/06/telling-gulliver-no/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/12/06/telling-gulliver-no/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 07 Dec 2024 02:58:49 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7817" class="post-7817 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Telling Gulliver No&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, I received my monthly bank statement from town hall. I received 68,500 bells in interest this month. The amount grows a little bit each month.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I shot down Gulliver&amp;#8217;s UFO, and I went over to meet him. But when he asked me for help recovering his UFO parts, I said no! I wanted to see how he&amp;#8217;d respond, and he didn&amp;#8217;t disappoint. First, he said he must&amp;#8217;ve misunderstood me&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/gulliver-baffles-150x112.jpg" alt="Gulliver: The language of your people baffles my foreign ears! I think I misunderstood you." class="wp-image-7819" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And then he asked again, while also insulting my intelligence. 😆 As you&amp;#8217;d expect, this part just loops back if you say no again.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/gulliver-simpler-150x112.jpg" alt="Gulliver: I shall ask you again, using simpler words your alien mind can understand." class="wp-image-7818" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;As I searched for the missing parts, I stumbled onto this cool view of the UFO from across the river, during sunset.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/ufo-sunset-150x112.jpg" alt="A view of Gulliver and his UFO from across the river, at sunset." class="wp-image-7821" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Truffles asked me to deliver a letter to Curt, and I agreed to help out. Curt enjoyed the letter, and he said Truffles isn&amp;#8217;t all that bad!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/curt-truffles-150x112.jpg" alt="Curt: That Truffles isn't all that bad, fuzzball." class="wp-image-7822" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;I disagree.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But then as soon as he said it, he turned around and walked right into a pitfall! 😆 I didn&amp;#8217;t push him, and it wasn&amp;#8217;t even my pitfall! He saved me the trouble by doing it to himself! 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/curt-pit-150x112.jpg" alt="Curt struggles in a pitfall." class="wp-image-7823" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I returned to Truffles, and she thanked me&amp;#8230;but she didn&amp;#8217;t give me a reward. My pockets were full, unfortunately. (And she never mailed me a reward, either!)&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Once I found all of the UFO parts, Gulliver rewarded me with another compass.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Whitney asked me what I thought about her outfit. I said it made her look like a rock star, and she agreed. She said the outfit was a keeper.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/whitney-keeper-150x112.jpg" alt="Whitney: Tee hee! Yes, I am a rock goddess! This look is a keeper, snappy!" class="wp-image-7825" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But just a few seconds later, she said she was in a clothes rut and needed to update her look!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/whitney-look-150x112.jpg" alt="Whitney: I think I need to update my look and get more clothes, snappy!" class="wp-image-7826" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Tank was looking forward to the next flea market. He was trying to think of all the wonderful products he could sell.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tank-shabby-150x112.jpg" alt="Tank: Shabby shirts, sweaty rags, and too-tight pants..." class="wp-image-7827" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/tank-sell-150x112.jpg" alt="Tank: Man, I have SO much stuff to sell, yip yip!" class="wp-image-7828" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Remind me not to shop at Tank&amp;#8217;s house next time. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Caroline has still been sick with a cold, so I gave her more medicine Wednesday, yesterday, and today. Hopefully she&amp;#8217;ll be over this cold soon, because this is dragging on too long.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I posted my latest Wild World video today, episode 72. It covers highlights of the past three weeks or so, through yesterday. I hope you&amp;#8217;ll check it out!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing: Wild World #72" width="840" height="473" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dJ7kKaXZBuU?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Enjoy your weekend!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/12/06/telling-gulliver-no/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-12-06T21:58:49-05:00"&gt;December 6, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-12-06T21:58:50-05:00"&gt;December 6, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/gulliver-baffles.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Clock Trade - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2024/11/30/clock-trade/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2024/11/30/clock-trade/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Dec 2024 04:51:32 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18044" class="post-18044 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;The Clock Trade&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday, Moose the mouse was camping at the campsite. He said he just kept running and running until he got here.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241125_HNI_0066-250x150.jpg" alt="Moose: I was really focused on running. I ran and ran and ran. And when I looked up, I was in this town!" class="wp-image-18045" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Keep running, man. Keep running.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Mira asked me to catch a coelacanth for her!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241129_HNI_0068-250x150.jpg" alt="Mira: What I need now is to study a coelacanth to learn this tail-attack thing!" class="wp-image-18057" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I try to complete requests for villagers when I still need their photos, but a coelacanth is just &lt;em&gt;sooo &lt;/em&gt;rare. Besides, it wasn&amp;#8217;t even snowing! So I declined her request.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241129_HNI_0069-250x150.jpg" alt="Mira: Huh? Really? But it would be so easy for you, dude..." class="wp-image-18047" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;No it wouldn&amp;#8217;t. Do it yourself, superhero.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Hornsby gave me a leaf tee, and I decided to put it on. I know it&amp;#8217;s not very wintry, but I needed to change my clothes. They were getting a little stinky. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241129_HNI_0070-250x150.jpg" alt="Me wearing a leaf tee that Hornsby gave me." class="wp-image-18046" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I played again a few hours later, and guess what? It &lt;em&gt;did &lt;/em&gt;start snowing, after all.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241129_HNI_0073-250x150.jpg" alt="Snow flurries fall in Forest." class="wp-image-18048" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It was too late to go back and accept a declined request, but Mira actually had another request for me. There was one problem&amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241130_HNI_0078-250x150.jpg" alt="Mira: Oh! I need to run something by you. I'm collecting signatures for the Practice-Waddling Day issue!" class="wp-image-18049" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It was for a petition! I can&amp;#8217;t travel to another town to collect signatures, so I had to decline this request too! Oof, two in one day? I&amp;#8217;m &lt;em&gt;never &lt;/em&gt;going to get her photo. 😖&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Remember the Mouth of Truth I gave Rolf last month? I found it up for sale in Re-Tail today!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241130_HNI_0080-250x150.jpg" alt="Reese: Oh, the Mouth of Truth? This item belongs to Rolf from here in Forest." class="wp-image-18050" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I bought it back, even though it cost me over 6,000 bells. And when I went back outside, Aurora told me she had a dream about a Mouth of Truth. Sounds like a nightmare. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241130_HNI_0082-250x150.jpg" alt="Aurora: I keep having this dream about a Mouth of Truth." class="wp-image-18051" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She wanted to buy mine for 2,280 bells, and I agreed to the deal. It&amp;#8217;s kinda funny how this keeps getting passed around between me and my villagers. Maybe it&amp;#8217;s why none of us have any fingers. 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;If you didn&amp;#8217;t get that joke, it&amp;#8217;s because of the legend of the real &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bocca_della_Verit%C3%A0" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"&gt;Mouth of Truth&lt;/a&gt; in Italy. Supposedly, it&amp;#8217;s like a lie detector. Put your hand in its mouth, and then say something. If you&amp;#8217;re lying, legend says it will bite off your hand. 😛&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Fortunately, Mira had an easier request for me today: Catch a river fish. I caught a bitterling for her, and she rewarded me with a lightning tee.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;There was another camper at the campsite today: Phoebe the ostrich&amp;#8230;or phoenix. She&amp;#8217;s much better to have around than Moose, that&amp;#8217;s for sure. But of course, my town is full anyway.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241130_HNI_0091-250x150.jpg" alt="Phoebe, at the campsite: I'll have to remember this place! Sparky!" class="wp-image-18052" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Cube wanted to trade away his cube clock that I gave him! I guess he&amp;#8217;s trying to turn back time. But even more interestingly, he&amp;#8217;s trying to trade it for another clock!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241130_HNI_0092-250x150.jpg" alt="Cube: Let's make a deal! Wanna trade your cabin clock for my cube clock?" class="wp-image-18053" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;He had time on his side, but so did I.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I agreed that it was time to trade. After all, the deal was &lt;em&gt;second &lt;/em&gt;to none. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Later on, I regifted the cube clock to Inkwell when he asked me for some furniture. But he only gave me a fish in return!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241130_HNI_0095-250x150.jpg" alt="Inkwell: Oh! I might as well give you my old crucian carp as a reward!" class="wp-image-18054" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Man, that&amp;#8217;s a raw deal.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I finished up my night with a concert at Club LOL. I asked K.K. Slider for a random song, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Waltz&amp;#8221; for me. My former villagers Hamlet and Pashmina were also at the show.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241130_HNI_0001-250x150.jpg" alt="K.K. Slider performs at Club LOL." class="wp-image-18055" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;ll see you all again in December! Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2024/11/30/clock-trade/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-11-30T23:51:32-05:00"&gt;November 30, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-11-30T23:53:23-05:00"&gt;November 30, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/20241125_HNI_0066.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>First Flurries - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/11/30/first-flurries/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/11/30/first-flurries/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Dec 2024 03:27:40 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-7806" class="post-7806 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;First Flurries&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Forest had its first snow flurries of the season. Whitney the white wolf welcomed the winter weather, saying the cold air feels like it&amp;#8217;s scrubbing her insides clean. That&amp;#8217;s a weird way of wording that. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/whitney-scrub-150x112.jpg" alt="Whitney: When you breathe it in, it feels like it's scrubbing your insides clean!" class="wp-image-7808" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I spoke with Filbert, he told me that he left some sparkling cider outside overnight. But when he found it in the morning, it had turned into sherbet!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/filbert-sherbet-150x112.jpg" alt="Filbert: And it turned into sherbet! Huh huh huh! I'm so happy! It's delicious, yip yip!" class="wp-image-7807" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He was so happy about that&amp;#8230;until he asked me to catch a black bass for him and I declined. He was bummed out then. Sorry, squirrel.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Curt was already trying to move out of town! He&amp;#8217;s only lived in town for two weeks! Even though I don&amp;#8217;t care for Curt much, I don&amp;#8217;t like letting anyone move out after just two weeks. &lt;em&gt;(Well, unless it&amp;#8217;s someone I really hate, like Jambette or Yuka.)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Filbert told me that he&amp;#8217;s the undisputed champ of figure skating. Well, the undisputed champ of &lt;em&gt;watching &lt;/em&gt;figure skating on TV. 😉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/filbert-champ-150x112.jpg" alt="Filbert: When it comes to watching it on TV...well, I'm the undisputed champ!" class="wp-image-7809" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tonight, Bones asked me to make a delivery to Truffles&amp;#8230;for a bite. That&amp;#8217;s his new catchphrase, which I mentioned last week.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/bones-bite-150x112.jpg" alt="Bones: Come on, champ, can't you deliver it for me, for a bite?" class="wp-image-7810" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;A bite of food? Or are you going to bite me?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I took it over to Truffles, and the gift was a bold check shirt. Truffles called it a &amp;#8220;safe&amp;#8221; choice, despite the shirt&amp;#8217;s claim of being bold. 😛 When I returned to Bones, he rewarded me with some old flooring. Fortunately, no bites were bitten. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I headed over to the Roost in the museum, and K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Technopop&amp;#8221; for me. It&amp;#8217;s a pretty boring song when sung live.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/kk-113024-150x112.jpg" alt="K.K. Slider performs for me at The Roost." class="wp-image-7811" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After the show, I visited Caroline. She&amp;#8217;s sick with a cold, so I gave her some medicine. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;By contrast, Whitney was feeling really good. In fact, she thinks she&amp;#8217;s going to start playing lacrosse! That was random, but sure. Good luck with it, Whitney!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/whitney-lacrosse-150x112.jpg" alt="Whitney: It's been a while since I've worked out, y'know. Maybe I'll try lacrosse." class="wp-image-7812" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Does she realize it&amp;#8217;s a team sport, though? She&amp;#8217;s more of a lone wolf. 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;See you all next week!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c27d879b16e3317f0d6fa350680e5023?s=98&amp;#038;d=mm&amp;#038;r=g' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2024/11/30/first-flurries/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-11-30T22:27:40-05:00"&gt;November 30, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-11-30T22:32:11-05:00"&gt;November 30, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/whitney-scrub.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>MVP Bones - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/11/29/mvp-bones/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/11/29/mvp-bones/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 30 Nov 2024 04:59:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8471" class="post-8471 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;MVP Bones&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, Margie the elephant was camping at the campsite! I wouldn&amp;#8217;t mind having her around at some point, but I didn&amp;#8217;t want to kick anyone out to get her.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/margie-camper-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Margie, at the campsite: This place is so mellow and laid-back that I can tell already I'm going to go home from here feeling restored." class="wp-image-8474" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Just outside the tent, I caught this paper kite butterfly. Of course, I know it&amp;#8217;s a common bug, but I just really liked this screenshot for some reason. I don&amp;#8217;t know if it&amp;#8217;s the sunlight or the fact that I&amp;#8217;m centered in front of the tent, but something in this picture just draws me in aesthetically.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/paper-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="I caught a paper kite butterfly!" class="wp-image-8475" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Monday, Pascal popped up to tell me that rocks are the oysters of the land. He then gave me a pearl (in exchange for my scallop), and swam off.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/pascal-rocks-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Pascal: Rocks are the oysters of the land." class="wp-image-8476" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;And jellyfish are the pitfalls of the sea.&lt;br&gt;(New Leaf players will get this one.)&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, I recorded my full gameplay session and uploaded it as a video. It had been over a year since I posted such a gameplay video of New Horizons. So here it is, if you&amp;#8217;re interested:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="Animal Crossing: New Horizons - Noon Gameplay Session (30+ min.)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/RFRjijyzgxA?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday was Thanksgiving in the U.S., and that meant it was Turkey Day in New Horizons. Franklin the chef had tables set up in the plaza, and he asked me to help him gather ingredients for him.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/franklin2024-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Franklin, on Turkey Day: And no one knows feasting like turkeys, which is why they called in a professional, gobble gob." class="wp-image-8477" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;You&amp;#8217;re a professional gobble gob?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Louie was already eyeing Franklin in that pic. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I gathered up the ingredients I needed, one dish at a time. My villagers also helped with secret ingredients to make the dishes even better.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/bones-manure-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Bones, wearing a chef hat: OK, have you ever had manure? Wait, uh...I mean men...y'air. I did it!" class="wp-image-8478" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Okay, that was a bad example. But Bones actually did help me out a lot, giving me two of the secret ingredients I needed (a barred knifejaw and a Dungeness crab).&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/bones-crab-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="Bones: Hooray! Now my food'll get to be its yum-yum-yummiest self. Here, take my extra Dungeness crab." class="wp-image-8479" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;With his help, I completed the event with all four dishes and all four special ingredients. I hope you all had a good Turkey Day, harvest festival, and/or Thanksgiving!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/harvest2024-sm-250x141.jpg" alt="The complete Turkey Day feast." class="wp-image-8480" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Just for reference, here is the list of the four dishes, including the ingredients:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;clam chowder: 3 manila clams (secret ingredient: scallop)&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;pumpkin pie: orange pumpkin, yellow pumpkin (secret ingredients: green pumpkin, white pumpkin)&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;gratin: round mushroom, potato (secret ingredient: Dungeness crab)&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;meunière: sea bass, dab (secret ingredient: barred knifejaw)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, Flick was in town&amp;#8230;but I didn&amp;#8217;t have much to sell him. Just two wasps and a paper kite butterfly, in fact. 😆 He gave me a whopping 9,000 bells for them all. Ooh, I&amp;#8217;m rich now! 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I helped out Wisp twice this week. He gave me some terra-cotta flooring on Sunday night, and a popcorn snack set on Wednesday.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Enjoy your weekend, everyone! I&amp;#8217;ll see you next week.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/11/29/mvp-bones/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2024-11-29T23:59:00-05:00"&gt;November 29, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2024-11-30T02:04:25-05:00"&gt;November 30, 2024&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
